{
  "text": "Adrenal hormonal effects on glial cells and neurons have also been documented [CITATION_1] ), however we were not able to show that early variation in adrenal-based indicators was related to WM measures at age 19 in the current study. Beginning data collection of pubertal indices at age 9 may have been too late to capture early onset of adrenarche [CITATION_2] , or that adrenal hormones have less detectable effects on the diffusion characteristics we measured at age 19. Future research is needed to replicate these results based on direct measures of both gonadal and adrenal hormone levels to clarify relations between various puberty-induced changes and brain WM development.",
